      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "Pumice is an Obsidian community plugin that syncs your vault with a self-hosted gRPC server\n([pumice-server](https://github.com/search5/pumice-server)). The goal is to sync instantly, no\nmatter how many files are in the vault — files are streamed concurrently over a single gRPC-Web\n(HTTP/2) connection instead of one request per file, and delta comparison means only changed files\nare ever uploaded or downloaded.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Fast, self-hosted sync**: delta comparison uploads/downloads only what changed; content hashes\n  are cached so unchanged files are skipped without re-reading or re-hashing them on every sync.\n- **End-to-end encryption**: optionally encrypt vault content before it ever leaves the device — the\n  server only ever sees ciphertext. The password lives in the OS keychain, never in `data.json`.\n- **Version history**: browse and recover previous versions of any file (`syncHistoryModal`,\n  `fileRecoveryModal`), backed by physical backups on the server.\n- **Automatic local snapshots**: periodic local snapshots with configurable retention, independent\n  of server sync.\n- **Selective publishing**: publish chosen folders as a public site, rendered from Markdown on the\n  server.\n- **Browser-based login**: authenticate via the system browser (token handled through an\n  `obsidian://` callback) instead of copying a token by hand.\n- **Auth**: a token stored in the OS keychain (macOS Keychain / Windows Credential Manager / Linux\n  libsecret) — never in vault-synced files.\n- **Localization**: Korean and English, with more addable via `src/locales`.\n\nSee the [README](https://github.com/search5/pumice/blob/0.0.10/README.md) for the full settings\nreference and setup instructions.\n",
